OL,5, Millions of people on benefits are     
OL,6, missing out on cheaper broadband       
OL,7, tariffs because firms are failing to   
OL,8, promote them properly, the media       
OL,9, watchdog Ofcom has said.               
OL,11,FOnly around 3.5% of those eligible for 
OL,12,Fthe deals are currently on one.        
OL,14,FSocial tariffs are low-cost broadband  
OL,15,Fdeals offered to customers on benefits 
OL,16,Fand cost about #15 a month.            
OL,18,FThe average customer could save #140 a 
OL,19,Fyear by switching to one of these      
OL,20,Fdeals, consumer group Which? says.     
